es.<br>Maybe bank the Shieldstorm for (eventual) dragon raids. (definately need some WR bags.  a single tailored bp doesn't cut it for six 7+wt weapons.)<br>Get a 5/5 or 6/6 str/dex ring, or hold out for 29 when my cleric can imbue some Black Pearls for the deity-specific jewelry (Stats: Black pearl (Prexus): plat ring, DEX 5, WIS 5, AGI 5)<br>the only thing i've paid for is the weapons.  The rest... right place at the right time, i guess.<br>I gave that Sporali Defender's Blade to another Paladin who needed it more than I. (IE, no 1hs except Ghoulbane... were in the Hole and we needed a little more power... so thank you, muchly, and i won't mention names <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> )<br>I don't have much money to spend, under 500pp right now, plus, she's not my main... just the 'i'm frustrated and need to beat something up' toon, although I enjoy RPing her a lot <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   Just trying to maximize her potential at her level.  Also going to play her more when my Bard main hits the 52 &quot;Vox/Naggy Scale plateau', i think.<br>Suggestions/comments/criticism appreciated and welcomed. <p><center><table border="1" width=87% bordercolor="0000FF"><tr><td><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=95465">Mileron</a></td><td>Singer of the 49th</td><td><a href="http://www.kenned.com/chp">Crusaders of the High Plains</a></td></tr><tr><td>Miradorn</td><td>Summoner of the 19th</td><td>Xegony</td></tr><tr><td><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=116169">Immarrana</td><td>Crusader of the OceanLord</td><td>(click names for Magelo)</td></tr></table></center></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/bpaladinsofnorrath.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=dyermaker>Dyermaker</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Knight Of the Realm</span><br>  Posts: 74<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(3/21/02 6:30:52 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathfrm12.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=262.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: 22 Paladin...</span><hr size=1> You might want to see if you can get a set of Gauntlets of the Black. On my server they sell for about 100PP, which meets your budget. Better AC and very Paladin friendly stats. I am level 42 and I haven't found anything I would be willing to swap them for.<br><br>I skipped it myself, but you might want to look into the Silent Watch Shield quest. The shield is also a back slot item, which is an AC and WIS boost over your banded cloak. If I am not mistaken, I think you can do the quest at your level.<br><br>And you might be a little too low to wander alone, but the Cougarskin Mask in Ice Clad is a great mask. Very simple quest, you can buy the HQ cougar skin and Mammoth Meat pretty inexpensively. If you have a friend who will keep you company in case anything causes trouble on the trip, you'll have a nice cheap upgrade.<br><br> <p>Dyermaker Merdinho -- The Lost Paladin and Lil'Bastard<BR>42 Paladin of Tunare, Quellious Server<BR>Profiles: <A HREF="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=32626">Magelo<A> -- <A HREF="http://everquest.allakhazam.com/db/userinfo.html?char=16712">Allakhazam</A> --<A HREF="http://eq.castersrealm.com/players/view_profile.asp?Id=3366">Caster's Realm</A><BR>Lil'Bastard Clan: <A HREF="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=32626">Dyermaker</A> | <A HREF="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=91012">Chapado</A> | <A HREF="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=115022">Chiad</A>  | <A HREF="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=82578">Malvado</A> | <A HREF="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=92554">Narnya</A> | <A HREF="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=111438">Solyony</A> <BR></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uangelsyn.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Angelsyn</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://members.aol.com/tdlutenatenjou/icon_keyne.jpg" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 204<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(3/21/02 8:16:24 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathfrm12.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=262.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://members.aol.com/tdlutenatenjou/icon_keyne.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: 22 Paladin...</span><hr size=1> Okay... what happened to those Twilight Sea Quest gloves you had? <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br><br>1) Cougarskin Mask is an easy quest for a good face piece.<br>2) Helmet of Ro is easily obtainable by your Bard, and will help out alot at these lower levels. (After ~40, you'll want the DW Helm all the time for the AC.)<br>3) Adamantite Epaulets are a much better shoulder piece for you.<br>4) The Shield of the Silent Watch quest is <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> not</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> something you can easily get at 22.  If you've got a high level nuker (Enchanter works best, I've found) then you can take care of the DE in Highkeep... otherwise either get some strong help or wait.<br>5) Dire Wolf Fur Cloak is a nice cloak and can be MQed.  Have your Bard pick up the Skinning Stones and turn them in, then switch to the Pally to turn in the Dire Wolf Fur.  (Did this with my Warrior.)<br>6) A Centi Warhammer would be a great replacement for the Stien &amp; Velium Warhammer.<br>7) Gauntlets of the Black are <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> the</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> Paladin Gauntlets.<br><!--EZCODE EMOTICON START 8) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/glasses.gif ALT="8)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  A Centi Shortsword (or preferably Centi Longsword) is a great 1h-slash weapon.<br>9) Replace that +2 Sta earring with something... Cougar Claw, Orc Fang, Forest Loop... Heck, I've got a spare +3 Str earring I can give you!<br>10) I hope you're doing Tailoring... I'd love to help you gather up some Terrorantula Silk and make some armour.  Expensive, but worth it.  (Just need skill ~115 for the Imbued Silk, it appears.)  Sleeves &amp; Greaves would be your best pieces there. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/umileron.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Mileron</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_bluespot.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 13<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(3/21/02 8:52:03 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathfrm12.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=262.topic&index=3>Reply</a>    <br>Community Supporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: 22 Paladin...</span><hr size=1> Put them on, but the loss of Dex takes her to 76, and just keep missing stuff, even with 1hs, 2hs, 2hp maxed.  On dark and light blues.  Could use the 3 wisdom, but the dex helps a bit more.<br><br>The paladin will most likely never be solo, though she's got the power to do so... her IC sister is a cleric, and they go everywhere together. (so far.)<br>The cleric will be doing the tailoring, and I've already got three Terrorantula swatches... just need to do the skillups to 119 or so... (need lots and lots of bear pelts and grizzlybear skins)<br>I've got a warrior that I can rip some cougarclaws off of... he also has a Jagged Blade of Mourning (12/25, dex +10 1hs) that i could take... how bout that?<br>I wish there were decent ac/str/wis earrings, though i understand there's some ac/hp/mana ones...<br>Also I'll eventually think about doing Soulfire, for grins... right of passage and all that.<br>Mostly, though, I only used the Bard for initial outfitting and want to try to use the paladin to further herself, if that makes any sense. <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/umileron.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Mileron</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_bluespot.gif" BORDER=0> at: 3/21/02 10:08:52 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uangelsyn.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Angelsyn</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://members.aol.com/tdlutenatenjou/icon_keyne.jpg" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 211<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(3/21/02 1:34:08 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathfrm12.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=262.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://members.aol.com/tdlutenatenjou/icon_keyne.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: 22 Paladin...</span><hr size=1> Jagged Blade of Mouring is an excellent choice.<br><br>If you're worried about Dex, Gauntlets of Ro &gt; Iksar Scaled Gauntlets (I have a pair, a Mold &amp; a bar of Ronium if you're interested in a pair.)<br><br>P.S. I've got a Level 24 Warrioress (Stumbles) up in the Bazaar.  I've found that hunting in Netherbian Lair (with a partner) is pretty great xp. <p></p><i></i></td></tr>